{
  "text": "Yttrium sesquioxide (yttria) was chosen for investigation because of its high melting temperature of 24l0 0 C (1) and its very low thermal neutron cross section of 1.38 barns [CITATION_1] . An anomaly in the heat content (2) and internal friction (3) at 1057 0 0 was also of inter~st.",
  "correct_citation": {
